# Generated drizzle metadata snapshots are kept; drizzle journals stay versioned.
# Local Postgres data volume is named, not bind-mounted — nothing to ignore.

# Excel-import fuzz failure dumps (per S5 F-S1). The fuzz harness writes
# adversarial-byte samples + meta files under this path on failing cases.
# Some scenarios embed prototype-pollution payloads, bidi spoofing strings,
# and corrupted-xlsx bytes; under no circumstances should these blobs
# (synthetic or, worse, locally-substituted real workbook bytes) land in
# git. See docs/release-1-fuzzing-findings.md.
packages/excel-import/test/fuzz/failures/
!packages/excel-import/test/fuzz/failures/.gitkeep
